OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGovernment urged to fix    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ftouring 'crisis' in Europe 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The government should appoint a touring
OL,6, "tsar" to unravel the red tape facing  
OL,7, British musicians in Europe, a         
OL,8, cross-party group of MPs and peers has 
OL,9, said.                                  
OL,11,FThey would need to tackle the soaring  
OL,12,Fcosts of obtaining visas and           
OL,13,Ftransporting instruments that bands    
OL,14,Fhave encountered since Brexit.         
OL,16,FSome orchestras face bills of #5,000   
OL,17,Fevery time they play abroad, said the  
OL,18,FAll-Party Parliamentary Group on Music.
OL,20,FIt added the industry faced a "crisis" 
OL,21,Fthat required "urgent" action.         
